<paragraph id="FD79397D51E4FB0BB3AC29283C72B586" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">
<taxonomicName id="BE2B06FCE2F7CF4D60006A77417ED45F" authority="Vill." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Herniaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="null" pageNumber="846" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpina">
Herniaria 
<normalizedToken id="61DFBF5ACD1D101AC011589DAD1A3AD6" originalValue="alpína" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">alpina</normalizedToken>
Vill.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="37B803FAD3142E798E0C26C47668F2E7" pageId="null" pageNumber="846" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="68A20DBD3BDCA6464A5AE36E8EE7D9D0" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Alpen-Bruchkraut</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="D8F1668ACB418F35FAA99163448D3432" pageId="null" pageNumber="846" type="description">
<paragraph id="DCE6A74BCCACAE783BB0AAFB7061A971" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">
Ausdauernd; flach dem Boden anliegend. Stengel kriechend, stark verzweigt, 
<normalizedToken id="B1B6DBC7F2FB0E44C813254D65E68C96" originalValue="rückwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">rueckwaerts</normalizedToken>
abstehend behaart (Haare 0,1-0,3 mm lang). 
<normalizedToken id="780137F4AD49D4A6D5DA76FF08FF1161" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
oval, stumpf, 
<emphasis id="5FE5DCABD5FD0F5393551CC3C91A8C38" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">1,5</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="D20F83D84E7D6E6C9B6E93B581BD242D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">4,5 mm lang, 1</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="A4840E8A2F51746B70B7C82769DC6E4A" originalValue="½" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">1/2</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="D4F4198FB1A7759EEDBB859F4C8041CB" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">-2</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="D5DDEF6BDC77DDEE20628AF63EA1B50F" originalValue="½" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">1/2</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="36D168DB4CC297E4356683F9E7569B59" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">
mal so lang wie breit, am Rand und seltener auch etwas auf den 
<normalizedToken id="53928F47259C1C12F0354FEA38A20BA2" originalValue="Flächen" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Flaechen</normalizedToken>
behaart. 
<normalizedToken id="C0F41EB4520DA45FAAB8AAC728887129" originalValue="Nebenblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Nebenblaetter</normalizedToken>
0,5-1,5 mm lang
</emphasis>
, behaart. 
<emphasis id="619F572EC7EB3AE3FFD2853C933A667C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">
<normalizedToken id="6832E7BE6842E04512A4158FF07B2410" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Blueten</normalizedToken>
sehr kurz gestielt. Freie 
<normalizedToken id="0F561F4D6EECD1CADBD8F20EEF949BCA" originalValue="Kelchblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Kelchblaetter</normalizedToken>
0,8-1,5 mm lang
</emphasis>
, stumpf, zerstreut behaart. Frucht etwa so lang wie der Kelch. - 
<normalizedToken id="7BC0FA2420620B8E058153AE5E6D72F2" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F4914D889FC7F95A55AF5F6F9AEEC79" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">
<emphasis id="6F7507D5B6161E9F9470E75BE4FD7D97" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Zytologische Angaben. 2n = 18:</emphasis>
Material aus dem Wallis (Favarger 1959Favarger 1965).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A53030DBAAD7BC053A7F03AF93AF3711" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">
<emphasis id="06897A21E79E09F76285C046DB9065C7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Standort.</emphasis>
Alpin, selten subalpin (herabgeschwemmt). Lockere, steinige, meist kalkhaltige 
<normalizedToken id="0EBA40EADA3467E1156567ECC493CD4C" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Boeden</normalizedToken>
. Feiner Felsschutt, 
<normalizedToken id="E3C317C4F26000E38695E2DE6985A7A4" originalValue="Moränen" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Moraenen</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C5AC2BD8F78C489D628AD50E7292577" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">
<emphasis id="C41A764A00FE1839CABFAD3DE83D824B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">
Verbreitung. Mittel- und 
<normalizedToken id="6F0113A63879BC10AD262E8BD666E095" originalValue="südeuropäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">suedeuropaeische</normalizedToken>
Gebirgspflanze
</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="E8D1D7E0980842101EAB6AB718F709B8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">westlich</emphasis>
): 
<normalizedToken id="CFD1B4F37E5FA2DD1A79A79B140DDE42" originalValue="Pyrenäen" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Pyrenaeen</normalizedToken>
, Alpen (
<normalizedToken id="75FF5683CE40EF7F517A2706CB83BAF0" originalValue="ostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">ostwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Tirol), Apennin. - Im Gebiet: Savoyen (Maurienne, Tarentaise), Wallis (
<normalizedToken id="D6C1A630B48ADBC7B79BD72B26A75761" originalValue="Südkette" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Suedkette</normalizedToken>
), Aostatal, Valsesia (Alpe Granos), 
<normalizedToken id="CA907D935D72E1646866F228D2C3AB6D" originalValue="nördliches" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">noerdliches</normalizedToken>
Tessin (Val Bavona, Val Antabbia, Val Lavizzara, Val Bedretto, Val Piora), 
<normalizedToken id="B53A164E1E9607C0004B8124ABD4388C" originalValue="Graubünden" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Graubuenden</normalizedToken>
(
<normalizedToken id="16B6B2D1D8DFF12B272005D2640BACCE" originalValue="Urdenpaß" pageId="null" pageNumber="846">Urdenpass</normalizedToken>
, Vals?, Albula?, Fimberjoch), Vorarlberg (Vermuntgletscher); ziemlich selten.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
